Mike has a total of 28 GB of disk space and needs to back up files that take up 26 GB. To find out how much space he would have left, we subtract the backup size from the available space.

\[
\begin{align*}
\text{Available space} &= 28 \ \text{GB} \\
\text{Backup size} &= 26 \ \text{GB} \\
\text{Space left} &= \text{Available space} - \text{Backup size} \\
&= 28 \ \text{GB} - 26 \ \text{GB} \\
&= 2 \ \text{GB}
\end{align*}
\]

**Answer:**
\boxed{2}

